There are also hard exudates visible, particularly in the macular region. Cotton wool spots are present, indicating localized retinal ischemia. The retinal fundus image shows several microaneurysms and dot hemorrhages scattered throughout the retina. There are also multiple hard exudates, particularly in the macular region. No signs of neovascularization, cotton wool spots, or venous beading are observed. The optic disc appears normal with clear margins.

The retinal fundus image shows several signs indicative of diabetic retinopathy. There are multiple microaneurysms visible as small red dots scattered throughout the retina. Hemorrhages are present, appearing as larger, darker red areas. There are also numerous hard exudates, which are yellowish-white spots, particularly concentrated in the central and upper regions of the retina. Cotton wool spots, which are soft, white patches, are also visible, indicating localized retinal ischemia. The optic disc appears normal, and there is no evidence of neovascularization or significant venous beading.
